Module com.example.historian
Package com.example.historian.models.photo

Class Photo

java.lang.Object
com.example.historian.models.photo.Photo
public class Photo extends Object
The Photo class represents a photo with an ID, date, description, tags, location, and image data.

  • Constructor Details

    • Photo

      public Photo(byte[] image, String imageType, String description, int uploaderAccountId)
      Constructs a Photo object with the specified image data, image type, and description.

      Because there are so many different permutations of arguments that can be passed into the constructor I have just decided to keep it at requiring an image where other metadata can be added after creation.

      Parameters:
      image - the image data as a byte array
      imageType - the type of the image (e.g., "jpg", "png")
      description - the description of the photo
